Simplify $\frac{\sqrt{507}}{\sqrt{48}}-\frac{\sqrt{175}}{\sqrt{112}}$.

$\frac{\sqrt{507}}{\sqrt{48}}-\frac{\sqrt{175}}{\sqrt{112}} = \frac{\sqrt{507}}{\sqrt{48}} - \frac{\sqrt{175}}{\sqrt{112}} = \frac{\sqrt{3 \cdot 13 \cdot 13}}{\sqrt{3 \cdot 16}} - \frac{\sqrt{5 \cdot 5 \cdot 7}}{\sqrt{7 \cdot 16}} = \frac{\sqrt{3 \cdot 169}}{\sqrt{3 \cdot 16}} - \frac{\sqrt{25 \cdot 7}}{\sqrt{7 \cdot 16}} = \frac{\sqrt{3} \cdot \sqrt{169}}{\sqrt{3} \cdot \sqrt{16}} - \frac{\sqrt{25} \cdot \sqrt{7}}{\sqrt{7} \cdot \sqrt{16}} = \frac{\sqrt{169}}{\sqrt{16}} - \frac{\sqrt{25}}{\sqrt{16}} = \frac{13}{4} - \frac{5}{4} = \frac{13 - 5}{4} = \frac{8}{4} = 2$

Final Answer: $\boxed{2}$
